			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Hazardous solid waste is a term used in the hazardous waste management program. It is defined by the EPA's hazardous waste regulations under RCRA Subtitle C. This type of waste can cause substantial harm to human health and the environment if improperly handled. It can take the form of solids, liquids, sludges, or contained gases, and is primarily generated by chemical production, manufacturing, and other industrial activities. A solid waste derived from a hazardous waste is not considered hazardous when it no longer exhibits any characteristic of hazardous waste.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">危险固体废物是危险废物管理计划中的一个术语。此类废物如果处理不当，会对人类健康和环境造成严重危害。它可以是固体、液体、淤泥或含有气体的形式，主要由化学生产、制造和其他工业活动产生。从危险废物衍生而来的固体废物，如果不再表现出危险废物的任何特征，则不被视为危险废物。</common:generalComment>
